    "42996067": {
      "title": "Growth or decay of cosmological inhomogeneities as a function of their equation of state",
      "abstract": "We expand Einstein's equations in the synchronous gauge in terms of a purely space-dependent, ``seed,'' metric. The (nonlinear) solution accurately describes a universe inhomogeneous at scales larger than the Hubble radius. We show that the inhomogeneities grow or decay, as time increases, depending on the equation of state for the matter (supposed to be a perfect fluid). We then consider the case when matter is a scalar field with an arbitrary potential. Finally we discuss the generality of the model and show that it is an attractor for a class of generic solutions of Einstein's equations."
    }
  }
